Class TestTriplePatternBuilder

    junit.framework.Test

    public class TestTriplePatternBuilder
extends AbstractBigdataExprBuilderTestCase
    Test suite for building up triple patterns, including those which are covered by the property paths extension in SPARQL 1.1 (a triple pattern which a constant in the predicate position is treated by the sesame SPARQL grammar as a degenerate case of a property path.)
    Version:
    $Id: TestGroupGraphPatternBuilder.java 5064 2011-08-21 22:50:55Z thompsonbry $

    Bryan Thompson

      • test_bnode_bracket_syntax_01

        public void test_bnode_bracket_syntax_01()
                                  throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                                         TokenMgrError,
                                         ParseException
        Unit test for blank node "[]" syntax. 
         PREFIX  : 
 SELECT * { [] :p "v" }
        Note that [] is a blank node and is represented as an anonymous variable.

        Note: blank nodes are translated into anonymous variables in the parse tree before the bigdata AST model is generated.

        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException

      • test_bnode_bracket_syntax_03

        public void test_bnode_bracket_syntax_03()
                                  throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                                         TokenMgrError,
                                         ParseException
        Unit test for blank node "[]" syntax. 
         PREFIX  : 
 SELECT * { [ :p "v" ] :q "w" }
        Note that this has exactly the same interpretation as: 
         PREFIX  : 
 SELECT * {
   _:b57 :p "v" .
   _:b57 :q "w"
 }
        assuming that the blank node is given the identity _:b57.

        Note: blank nodes are translated into anonymous variables in the parse tree before the bigdata AST model is generated.

        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException

      • test_rdf_collections_01

        public void test_rdf_collections_01()
                             throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                                    TokenMgrError,
                                    ParseException
        Unit test for the RDF Collections syntax (from SPARQL 1.1 Last Call Working Draft). 
         PREFIX  : 
 PREFIX rdf: 
 SELECT * { (1 ?x 3 4) :p "w" . }
        has exactly the same interpretation as 
             _:b0  rdf:first  1 ;
           rdf:rest   _:b1 .
     _:b1  rdf:first  ?x ;
           rdf:rest   _:b2 .
     _:b2  rdf:first  3 ;
           rdf:rest   _:b3 .
     _:b3  rdf:first  4 ;
           rdf:rest   rdf:nil .
     _:b0  :p         "w" .
        where _:b0, etc. are blank nodes not appearing elsewhere in the query.

        Note: blank nodes are translated into anonymous variables in the parse tree before the bigdata AST model is generated.

        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException

      • test_rdf_collections_02

        public void test_rdf_collections_02()
                             throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                                    TokenMgrError,
                                    ParseException
        Unit test for the RDF Collections syntax (from SPARQL 1.1 Last Call Working Draft). 
         PREFIX  : 
 PREFIX rdf: 
 SELECT * { ( (1 [:p :q] ( 2 ) ) }
        has exactly the same interpretation as 
             _:b0  rdf:first  1 ;
           rdf:rest   _:b1 .
     _:b1  rdf:first  _:b2 .
     _:b2  :p         :q .
     _:b1  rdf:rest   _:b3 .
     _:b3  rdf:first  _:b4 .
     _:b4  rdf:first  2 ;
           rdf:rest   rdf:nil .
     _:b3  rdf:rest   rdf:nil .
        where _:b0, etc. are blank nodes not appearing elsewhere in the query.

        Note: blank nodes are translated into anonymous variables in the parse tree before the bigdata AST model is generated.

        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException

      • test_base_01

        public void test_base_01()
                  throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                         TokenMgrError,
                         ParseException
        Unit test for BASE declaration. 
         BASE 
 PREFIX dc: 
 SELECT $title
 WHERE {  dc:title ?title }
        Note: There is a trailing / on the BASE URI declaration for this example.

        Note: This also uses the alternative $title syntax, but $title and ?title are the same variable.

        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException

      • test_base_02

        public void test_base_02()
                  throws org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException,
                         TokenMgrError,
                         ParseException
        Unit test for BASE declaration. 
         BASE 
 PREFIX dc: 
 SELECT $title
 WHERE {  dc:title ?title }
        Note: There is a trailing # on the BASE URI declaration for this example. Per RFC3986, the fragment must be stripped from the base URI before it is used for resolution.

        Note: This also uses the alternative $title syntax, but $title and ?title are the same variable.

        Throws:
        org.openrdf.query.MalformedQueryException
        TokenMgrError
        ParseException
